    <note>Ma(2) Chiguo [24703] According to Guangdong TZ (Jiajing ed.), 20.60a-60b, Chiguo founded the Xinhui Ma(2) lineage when he migrated there during Zhao(1) Gaozong's reign. Xinhui Xiangtu zhi, p. 68, also traces the Ma(2) of Jinzi jie (street), to Chiguo and not that as of ca. 1911, there were less than one hundred resident Ma(2), which suggests that the major portion of the lineage may have lived in the splinter county, Taishan (Cantonese, Toisan). Both sources identify the 1181 jinshi, Xiji, as Chiguo's son. See also documentation for Ma(2) Dingguo [24701]. Guangdong TZ (Jiajing ed.), 11.18a.</note>
